description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Wehave an excellent opportunity for an enthusiastic and motivated Senior Pharmacy Services Assistant who already holds an NVQ/QCF Level 2 Pharmacy Service Skills Certificate and who has experience in either a hospital or community pharmacy setting, to join our forward thinking and generally all round fantastic pharmacy team based at ward level in the Oncology cluster at St James’ Hospital. This is an excellent opportunity to start a career in hospital pharmacy and&lt;span&gt; to&lt;/span&gt; play an important role in being part of a team working at ward level to deliver an exceptional medicine supply service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;By taking a patient first approach and through compassion and commitment you will focus on helping patients to optimise medicines use by involving them in making decisions about their medicines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will collaborate with other teams, communicating effectively to ensure a safe, seamless integrated transfer of care for our patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be joining a team providing an integrated delivery of medicines to our inpatients to ensure cost effective, safe and appropriate use of medicines.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must have excellent communication skills, be self-motivated, able to work on own initiative and enjoy a challenge. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is based at St James’ Hospital&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The vision for the hospital is to be a leading provider of healthcare, providing the highest quality of care and treatment to our patients.The post holder will provide a variety of duties across the multi-speciality wards, including ordering and receipt of medicines, stock management, labelling &amp; dispensing, liaising with patients and other NHS staff, answering telephone queries and clerical duties. You will also help to support our dispensary at peak times.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;It is a requirement of the post to hold an &lt;strong&gt;NVQ / QCF Level 2 Pharmacy Service Skills Certificate&lt;/strong&gt;. Further training will be provided as necessary.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;There will be a commitment to Week-End, Late night and Bank Holiday rotas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquiries, please contact : Janet Murphy or Emma Handley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; Ext: 0113 2065893 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; e-mail: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;janet.murphy6@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
